text: Our age is curious in that it is possible to become a "traveled man" from the comfort of your room
In Tibet, the first thing a man does when he receives a guest in his home is to take him and show him his treasures and riches, his rare items, gold. Nothing impolite or prideful about this...

The skilled Asian traveler always expects something out of the ordinary to happen, because he knows otherworldly things happen not only in midnight, but also at noon, in the bazaar. So a man on a journey always keeps his eyes open, no matter where or when.

t. Roerich
